Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C.) In a large bowl, beat the egg yolks and sugar. Stir in the melted butter and flour. Add the lemon juice, water, and vinegar; mix together until filling is smooth. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 45 minutes, or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.